{
    "level": "B2",
    "intro": "In this topic, you will learn <strong>where the passive is appropriate</strong>, and where it is better to use the active state. We will also consider the <strong>most common mistakes</strong> that are made when using the passive voice.",
    "rules": [
        {
            "label": "Academic",
            "color": "emerald",
            "text": "The passive emphasizes <strong>objectivity</strong>:",
            "example": "The experiment was conducted..."
        },
        {
            "label": "News",
            "color": "blue",
            "text": "The passive focuses on the <strong>event, not the doer</strong>:",
            "example": "Three people were injured."
        },
        {
            "label": "Error",
            "color": "rose",
            "text": "The redundant passive <strong>complicates</strong> the text:",
            "example": "❌ The ball was kicked by him."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "1. Where the passive is APPROPRIATE",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Academic and scientific style",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "In <strong>scientific articles and studies</strong>, the passive gives the impression of objectivity and detachment.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The experiment was conducted over six months.",
                    "ua": "The experiment was conducted over six months."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The data were collected from 500 participants.",
                    "ua": "The data were collected from 500 participants."
                },
                {
                    "en": "It has been demonstrated that...",
                    "ua": "It has been demonstrated that..."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The results were analyzed using SPSS software.",
                    "ua": "The results were analyzed using SPSS software."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Instructions and recipes",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "In <strong>instructions</strong>, the passive focuses on the process, not the doer.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The mixture should be stirred for 5 minutes.",
                    "ua": "The mixture should be stirred for 5 minutes."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The device must be turned off before cleaning.",
                    "ua": "The device must be turned off before cleaning."
                },
                {
                    "en": "First, the ingredients are combined.",
                    "ua": "First, the ingredients are combined."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "News and reports",
            "color": "blue",
            "description": "In <strong>news</strong>, the passive focuses on events and victims when the perpetrator is unknown or unimportant.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Three people were injured in the accident.",
                    "ua": "Three people were injured in the accident."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The bank was robbed yesterday.",
                    "ua": "The bank was robbed yesterday."
                },
                {
                    "en": "A new law has been passed by Parliament.",
                    "ua": "A new law has been passed by Parliament."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Official documents",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "In <strong>business correspondence and documents</strong>, the passive adds formality.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Your application has been received.",
                    "ua": "Your application has been received."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Payment is required within 30 days.",
                    "ua": "Payment is required within 30 days."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Applicants will be notified by email.",
                    "ua": "Applicants will be notified by email."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "2. Where it is BEST to use the asset",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "When the performer is important",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "If the <strong>artist is the key information</strong>, the asset sounds more natural.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "❌ The goal was scored by Messi.",
                    "ua": "❌ The goal was scored by Messi."
                },
                {
                    "en": "✅ Messi scored the goal.",
                    "ua": "✅ Messi scored the goal."
                },
                {
                    "en": "❌ The book was written by J.K. Rowling.",
                    "ua": "❌ The book was written by J.K. Rowling."
                },
                {
                    "en": "✅ J.K. Rowling wrote the book.",
                    "ua": "✅ J.K. Rowling wrote the book."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Spoken language",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "In <strong>daily communication</strong> the active sounds simpler and more natural.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "❌ The cake was eaten by me.",
                    "ua": "❌ The cake was eaten by me."
                },
                {
                    "en": "✅ I ate the cake.",
                    "ua": "✅ I ate the cake."
                },
                {
                    "en": "❌ The door was opened by Tom.",
                    "ua": "❌ The door was opened by Tom."
                },
                {
                    "en": "✅ Tom opened the door.",
                    "ua": "✅ Tom opened the door."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Shorter sentences",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "The active is often <strong>shorter and clearer</strong>, especially with a by-phrase.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "❌ Mistakes were made by me.",
                    "ua": "❌ Mistakes were made by me."
                },
                {
                    "en": "✅ I made mistakes.",
                    "ua": "✅ I made mistakes."
                },
                {
                    "en": "❌ The report was completed by the team.",
                    "ua": "❌ The report was completed by the team."
                },
                {
                    "en": "✅ The team completed the report.",
                    "ua": "✅ The team completed the report."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Dynamic actions",
            "color": "rose",
            "description": "For <strong>fast, dynamic actions</strong> the asset transmits energy better.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "❌ The ball was kicked by the player.",
                    "ua": "❌ The ball was kicked by the player."
                },
                {
                    "en": "✅ The player kicked the ball.",
                    "ua": "✅ The player kicked the ball."
                },
                {
                    "en": "❌ The car was driven by her.",
                    "ua": "❌ The car was driven by her."
                },
                {
                    "en": "✅ She drove the car.",
                    "ua": "✅ She drove the car."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "3. Error: \"by people/someone\" is a redundant agent",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Error",
            "color": "rose",
            "title": "Redundant \"by people\" or \"by someone\".",
            "wrong": "English is spoken by people here.",
            "right": "✅ English is spoken here."
        },
        {
            "label": "Error",
            "color": "amber",
            "title": "Redundant \"by them\" without specifics.",
            "wrong": "The decision was made by them.",
            "right": "✅ The decision was made. (якщо \"вони\" неважливі)"
        },
        {
            "label": "Error",
            "color": "sky",
            "title": "General executor in the passive.",
            "wrong": "It is believed by everybody that...",
            "right": "✅ It is believed that... / Everybody believes that..."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "4. Error: Wrong V3 (Past Participle)",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Incorrect verbs",
            "color": "rose",
            "title": "Confusion with irregular shapes.",
            "wrong": "The window was breaked. / was broke.",
            "right": "✅ The window was broken."
        },
        {
            "label": "Ending -ed",
            "color": "amber",
            "title": "Adding -ed to irregular verbs.",
            "wrong": "The letter was writed. / was sended.",
            "right": "✅ The letter was written. / was sent."
        },
        {
            "label": "V2 instead of V3",
            "color": "sky",
            "title": "Using Past Simple instead of V3.",
            "wrong": "The book was wrote by her.",
            "right": "✅ The book was written by her."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "5. Error: Time alignment",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Time be + V3",
            "color": "rose",
            "title": "Incorrect tense of the auxiliary be.",
            "wrong": "Yesterday, the report is written.",
            "right": "✅ Yesterday, the report was written."
        },
        {
            "label": "Present vs Past",
            "color": "amber",
            "title": "Confusion of the present and the past.",
            "wrong": "The project was completed tomorrow.",
            "right": "✅ The project will be completed tomorrow."
        },
        {
            "label": "Perfect tenses",
            "color": "sky",
            "title": "Skip been in the perfect tenses.",
            "wrong": "The work has done.",
            "right": "✅ The work has been done."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "6. Error: Redundant passive",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Excessive formality",
            "color": "rose",
            "title": "A passive where an active is better.",
            "wrong": "The coffee was drunk by me this morning.",
            "right": "✅ I drank coffee this morning."
        },
        {
            "label": "Complexity",
            "color": "amber",
            "title": "Complexity of simple sentences.",
            "wrong": "A good time was had by all.",
            "right": "✅ Everyone had a good time."
        },
        {
            "label": "Loss of clarity",
            "color": "sky",
            "title": "When the asset is clearer.",
            "wrong": "It was decided that the meeting would be postponed by the manager.",
            "right": "✅ The manager decided to postpone the meeting."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "7. When it is a liability and when it is an asset - a quick check",
    "intro": "Table for choosing between an asset and a liability:",
    "rows": [
        {
            "en": "Виконавець невідомий",
            "ua": "Виконавець невідомий",
            "note": "My car was stolen."
        },
        {
            "en": "Виконавець неважливий",
            "ua": "Виконавець неважливий",
            "note": "English is spoken here."
        },
        {
            "en": "Виконавець важливий",
            "ua": "Виконавець важливий",
            "note": "Messi scored the goal."
        },
        {
            "en": "Науковий/офіційний стиль",
            "ua": "Науковий/офіційний стиль",
            "note": "The data were analyzed."
        },
        {
            "en": "Розмовна мова",
            "ua": "Розмовна мова",
            "note": "I ate the cake."
        },
        {
            "en": "З \"by + очевидний agent\"",
            "ua": "З \"by + очевидний agent\"",
            "note": "Tom opened the door."
        }
    ],
    "warning": "📌 Ask yourself: <strong>Who is performing the action?</strong> If it is important - an asset. If not - passive."
}

{
    "title": "8. Tips for academic writing",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "When the passive is appropriate",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "In <strong>academic writing</strong>, the passive emphasizes the process and the result, not the author.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The samples were collected from three locations.",
                    "ua": "The samples were collected from three locations."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Statistical analysis was performed using SPSS.",
                    "ua": "Statistical analysis was performed using SPSS."
                },
                {
                    "en": "It was observed that temperature affects growth.",
                    "ua": "It was observed that temperature affects growth."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "When the asset is better",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "Even in academic style, the <strong>active</strong> is sometimes clearer.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Previous studies have shown that... (актив)",
                    "ua": "Previous studies have shown that... (актив)"
                },
                {
                    "en": "We analyzed the data using... (актив)",
                    "ua": "We analyzed the data using... (актив)"
                },
                {
                    "en": "The authors conclude that... (актив)",
                    "ua": "The authors conclude that... (актив)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Balance",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "<strong>Combine</strong> active and passive for variety and clarity.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "We collected samples (актив), which were then analyzed (пасив).",
                    "ua": "We collected samples (актив), which were then analyzed (пасив)."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The experiment was designed (пасив) to test our hypothesis (актив).",
                    "ua": "The experiment was designed (пасив) to test our hypothesis (актив)."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}
